      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:8:1:46:14",
      "relations": null,
      "text": [
        " قُلْتُ لِأَبِي جَعْفَرٍ (عليه السلام) يَقُولُ النَّاسُ تُطْوَى لَنَا الْأَرْضُ بِاللَّيْلِ كَيْفَ تُطْوَى قَالَ هَكَذَا ثُمَّ عَطَفَ ثَوْبَهُ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "<a id=\"_Toc492473621\">H 14938</a> – A number of our companions, Ahmad Bin Muhammad Bin Khalid, from Ismail Bin Mahraan, from Sayf Bin Umeyra, from Basheer Al-Nabaal, from Humraan Bin Ayn who said:",
          "<span class=\"first-chapter-phrase\"><span class=\"first-in-chapter character-i\">I</span> said to Abu Ja’far</span><sup>asws</sup>, ‘The people are saying the earth would fold up for us at night, how it would fold up?’ He<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘Like this’, then folded his<sup>asws</sup> cloth’. "
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "491. Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Hammaad Bin Usman, who has narrated the following: Abu Abdullah (a.s.) has said: ‘The earth folds up during the end of the night’."
        ]
      }
    }
